{
    "name": "Terror Shrike",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Terror Shrike",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "The terror shrike is a more powerful species of terror bird. Large terror bird flocks typically have one or two terror shrikes as leaders.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Monster Core 2",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 318",
                        "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 318",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 276
                    },
                    "page": 318
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Terror Bird",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Diatryma",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Diatrymas are 1st-level creatures akin to terror birds with a weak adjustment. These smaller kin of terror birds sport dark feathers and stand around 6 to 7 feet tall\u2014smaller than terror birds but no less ferocious. Diatrymas are mostly found in drier regions and sport small, orange beaks.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Monster Core 2",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 318",
                                "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 318",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 276
                            },
                            "page": 318
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "related_creatures",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Related Creatures",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Related Creatures",
                        "image": "Sidebar_4_RelatedCreatures.png"
                    },
                    "links": [
                        {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "weak",
                            "alt": "weak",
                            "game-obj": "MonsterTemplates",
                            "aonid": 23
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "text": "Terror birds aren't one species, but rather a family of deadly, flightless avian predators. All terror birds are capable of bursts of great speed and have powerful beaks that can tear apart the flesh of their prey. Most stalk large, open prairies and steppes, competing directly with other sizable predators such as big cats and wolves.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Monster Core 2",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 318",
                        "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 318",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 276
                    },
                    "page": 318
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
